## Security Features

### Container Security
- **Non-root execution**: All services run as unprivileged users
- **Minimal attack surface**: Only essential packages installed
- **Network isolation**: Services communicate through defined networks only
- **Resource limits**: CPU and memory constraints enforced

### Network Security
- **No host networking**: Services cannot access host network interfaces
- **Port restrictions**: Only explicitly exposed ports are accessible
- **Firewall rules**: Default deny with explicit allow rules

### Monitoring Security
- **Secure metrics**: Metrics endpoints protected and authenticated
- **Log security**: Sensitive data redaction and secure transport
- **Audit trails**: All access and configuration changes logged

## Usage

### Quick Start

```bash
# Clone and configure
copier copy /path/to/this/boilerplate my-service
cd my-service

# Build and start services
make build
make up

# Check health
make health-check
```

### Development

```bash
# View logs
make logs

# Access service shell
make shell

# Restart services
make restart
```

### Production Deployment

```bash
# Use production environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with production values

# Deploy with monitoring
make up

# Check monitoring
curl http://localhost:9090/targets
```

